snippet.title: 💥MOONSHOT🌑🚀👁️Remote Viewing The DEATH of a Lunar Lander - Beresheet. CRYPTOVIEWING PROJECT
snippet.description:
Beresheet was an unmanned lunar lander developed and launched by SpaceIL, a private Israeli company. The mission, which was launched on February 21, 2019, aimed to become the first Israeli spacecraft to land on the Moon. Although the mission ended in failure, the Beresheet mission was an important milestone for Israel's space program and for private space exploration.

The name Beresheet means "In the Beginning" in Hebrew and was chosen to symbolize the start of a new era in Israel's space exploration efforts. The spacecraft was launched aboard a SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket from Cape Canaveral, Florida. The mission was funded primarily by private donors and was designed to be a low-cost alternative to government-funded space programs.

The spacecraft was equipped with a suite of scientific instruments to study the lunar environment, including a magnetometer to study the Moon's magnetic field, a laser retroreflector to help measure the distance to the Moon from Earth, and a digital time capsule containing hundreds of files, including pictures and messages from Israeli children.

The spacecraft entered into a highly elliptical Earth orbit before executing a series of engine burns to propel it towards the Moon. The journey took seven weeks, during which the spacecraft traveled over 4 million miles (6.5 million kilometers).

On April 11, 2019, the spacecraft began its descent towards the Moon's surface. The landing process was highly automated, with the spacecraft using a combination of its engines and onboard computer to control its descent. However, during the final approach, the spacecraft's main engine failed, causing it to crash into the surface of the Moon.

Despite the mission's failure to land successfully, the Beresheet mission was an important milestone for private space exploration. It demonstrated that small, low-cost spacecraft can be developed and launched by private companies, paving the way for future commercial space exploration missions.

In addition, the Beresheet mission generated significant interest and excitement in Israel's space program. The mission was widely covered in the media and received support from high-profile figures, including Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu.

Looking forward, SpaceIL has stated that it plans to continue its efforts to develop and launch spacecraft for a variety of missions. The company has also expressed its commitment to inspiring and educating the next generation of Israeli scientists and engineers through its outreach and educational programs.

snippet.title: The Other Side of the Curve   Edward Riordan, Daz Smith, Debra Katz   Pilot Episode
snippet.description: Pilot Episode "The Other Side of the Curve Webcast Show", hosted by Debra Lynne Katz, with special guests remote viewers Daz Smit & Edward Riordan, two of the best and most innovative remote viewers on planet earth. These interviews get to the meat of the topics, (even down to the bones!) discussing issues you won't hear anywhere else because the guests aren't interested in starting at the beginning of their work/careers but instead discussing the issues they are most passionate about from where they are NOW, on "the other side of the curve". Daz Smith is editor of Eight Martini's Magazine and author of "Surfing the Psychic Internet"; "Controlled Remote Viewing" and Remote Viewing Dialogues". (www.remoteviewed.com). He runs some of the largest remote viewing and UFO websites on the internet. Edward Riordan has demonstrated how remote viewing is an art as much as it is an information gathering tool through offering thousands of hours of free on camera demonstrations through his own You Tube Page (www.erviewer.com). Debra Lynne Katz is the Director of the International School of Clairvoyance and author of "You Are Psychic"; "Extraordinary Psychic" and "Freeing the Genie Within" - as well as a film school graduate and former host of Sedona, Arizona's "The Psychic Explorer" television show. Topics in this 1.45 minute pilot episode include: Remote viewing is an art not just an outcome; Daz Smith's participation in compelling and controversial video projects hosted by the Farsight institute (including how he was tasked with Hitler and JFK at the very same time); issues around ownership of one's remote viewing sessions and creative works; Ingo Swann and the controversy over is training/monitoring necessary and helpful in remote viewing practice; and why aren't psychologists or other scientists more interested in the inner workings of a remote viewer's/psychic's mind and practices?!

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Chobham Armour's Boron Carbide Molecules
snippet.description: Critics of remote viewing and critical remote viewers will most likely dismiss this video as a total miss. Lucky for me, I dont care about the critics! A disciplined remote viewer hones the ability to provide information specific to a taskers or clients  needs. Sometimes, the viewer goes off and finds something far more interesting to explore. This is often the case for me, I am far more interested in finding things that fascinate me and exploring them. Remote viewing and or perceiving things that are on a molecular, atomic or subatomic level is for me the most exciting and interesting experiences I can have. I do this process we call remote viewing in order to have these type of experiences. Sometimes you just gotta get small!

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Glial Cells and our Physical Senses
snippet.description: Recent research is now showing the glial cells are directly related to our ability to sense our environment, ie touch, taste, smell etc. I am theorizing that these glial cells once infused with these second reality inputs, are what allows some remote viewers to have the experiences termed "bi-location", "site integration" or as I like to call "immersion" experiences in which the viewer feels and experiences the location as if they are physically there .

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: G-Cell Infusion/Illumination?
snippet.description: I am fascinated by the theory that these inputs may be infusing these glial cells with some form of quantum image or information of some form. Is that what is taking place? I do not know, but the only way for me to explore it is to experience it. So here I go....

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Glial Cell Interpenetration, Nervous System, Neurons
snippet.description: If the Glial cells are being infused and or illuminated with these holographic imputs from the second reality, is that how we "feel" as though we are actually at the target site? Is our nervous system being illuminated giving us a sense of being physically there? Are the glial cells surrounding our neurons being illuminated with these inputs as well causing our mental processing realms to become activated to begin the preconscious processes? Theory only goes so far, experience is the next step.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Glial Cell Interpenetration, Dr. Persinger
snippet.description: Do the inputs interpenetrate the glial cells and infuse them with some sort of quantum signature of specific points in time/space? Ingo Swann worked with Canadian neuroscientist Dr. Michael Persinger doing ESP experiments attempting to map the areas of the brain that became active when these experiences are taking place. Dr. Persinger postulates that the Glial cells that surround the central nervous system and the neurons of the brain not only deliver nutrients to the neurons, they also carry "information" as well. Are they the carriers of "information" that we experience in "remote viewing"? I am experimenting with the inputs infusing within my own glial cells, allowing me to experience the entire point in time and space, as opposed to only "describing" it. This is my lifes work and will continue to be.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Interpenetration, Delicate by Nature
snippet.description: The inputs are by there own nature very delicate, when we obtain them and begin processing them, we can distort them sometimes into oblivion. Per Websters dictionary interpenetrate is defined as:  to penetrate between, within, or throughout. The inputs that we obtain and have access to, interpenetrate between, within and throughout both our mind and nervous systems.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Immersion, the Experience
snippet.description: My goal with what we call remote viewing is to experience what Ingo Swann terms the "second reality".  What I am attempting to do is immerse myself within these inputs as I make my way through my own ESP core and into this other reality or dimension while describing my experience on video. This is  my journey.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Immersion, Second Reality
snippet.description: Remote viewing for me is less about describing remote targets then it is about experiencing what Ingo Swann calls the Second Reality. There is far more interesting things going on in this then data mining.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Nucleus,  Word to Form Conversion

I am interested in what is happening in the conversion of input to processed words and shapes. The exploration of this process is extensive and never ending. Each experience is unique and unrepeatable.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Touching the Second Reality
snippet.description: Remote viewing in my opinion is the ability to access another reality. The inputs that we are able to identify and objectify is what makes up a remote viewing session. I am far more interested in exploring this second reality, the quantum realm from which these inputs come from. These are my own explorations and my own opinions and are not the opinions of the remote viewing community in general.

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Destination Second Reality
snippet.description: Ingo Swann called it the "second reality", the realm in which these "remote viewing" inputs come from. What is its nature? What does it feel like? There is far more to this faculty then just "information gathering". We are attempting to access this quantum field, another reality. There is far more to it then just describing "targets".

snippet.title: Remote Viewing: Explorer or Data Miner?  What is the purpose?

These are good questions to ask oneself at some point in their remote viewing career. One would hope the remote viewer would ask themselves, "what is the purpose of all this effort"? This may open a conversation about what the individual is wanting or expecting from this pursuit. Are you an Explorer or a Data Miner? Both are valid and important, though some may find themselves stuck in one or the other. I personally am an explorer.

It was round and large, metallic and there were some kind of vent shafts inside of it that were emitting heat. I also perceived that the object was very old but newly discovered.

The Ocean X team is continuing its exploration of this strange object in an attempt to get some answers as to the origin and nature of this strange anomaly. The documentary "The Mystery Beneath" is soon to be released showing what has been discovered so far.
